# Java Development Guidelines

## Code Style
- Use 4-space indentation
- Max line length: 120 chars
- Follow Google Java Style Guide

## Naming Conventions
- Classes: PascalCase (UserService, OrderController)
- Methods: camelCase (getUserById, processOrder)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (MAX_RETRIES, DEFAULT_TIMEOUT)
- Packages: lowercase, reversed domain (com.company.module)

## Project Structure (Maven)
```
src/
├── main/
│   ├── java/com/{{PROJECT_NAME}}/
│   │   ├── controller/   # REST endpoints
│   │   ├── service/      # Business logic
│   │   ├── repository/   # Data access
│   │   ├── model/        # Domain entities
│   │   ├── dto/          # Data transfer objects
│   │   ├── config/       # Configuration classes
│   │   └── exception/    # Custom exceptions
│   └── resources/
│       └── application.yml
└── test/java/com/{{PROJECT_NAME}}/
```

## Layer Dependencies (Enforced)
- controller → service (allowed)
- controller → repository (forbidden, use service)
- service → repository (allowed)
- service → service (allowed, consider domain service)
- repository → service (forbidden)

## Best Practices
- Prefer immutability (final fields, records)
- Use Optional instead of null
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Use dependency injection (constructor injection)
- Avoid checked exceptions in API boundaries
- Use Lombok annotations sparingly

## Build Commands
- Maven: `mvn clean install`
- Gradle: `gradle build`
- Test: `mvn test` or `gradle test`
- Package: `mvn package` or `gradle jar`

## Quality Rules
- No System.out.println (use logger)
- Max method complexity: 10
- Max method lines: 50
- Max class lines: 500
- No magic numbers (use constants)